# Caddyfile
#
# Caddy handles TLS automatically via Let's Encrypt — no certbot needed.
# Set the DOMAIN env var on your EC2 instance (e.g. DOMAIN=movu.example.com).
# Caddy will obtain and renew a certificate for it automatically.
#
# For local testing, leave DOMAIN=localhost and Caddy will use its
# built-in local CA (self-signed, trusted on your machine via `caddy trust`).
#
# Only the Next.js web app is exposed publicly. The NestJS API and FastAPI RAG
# service are called server-side from within the Docker network and are never
# reachable from the internet.

{$DOMAIN:localhost} {
    reverse_proxy web:3000
}
